&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a qualified Emergency Nurse Practitioner to work in a fast paced , dynamic emergency department. Wythenshawe emergency department is seeking an enthusiastic, dedicated, highly motivated individual to come and join our Emergency Nurse Practitioner team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be opportunities to progress and develop your existing skills. The emergency department has a strong education and learning focus, and the successful applicant will be expected to actively participate in the teaching and training of student and junior ENPs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have responsibility for the assessment, evaluation and implementation of care for patients presenting with minor injury or illness. Using your established clinical skills, you will work independently as an ENP to deliver high-quality, evidence based care to this client group, with the support of the Nurse Consultant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to develop your scope of practice within local Trust guideline and policies. You will demonstrate an enthusiastic approach to care delivery and service improvement in order to work in this highly desirable area with a proactive multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will include shift working patterns which will be based at Wythenshawe Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
